<title type="html"><![CDATA[Concerning slots]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6053&amp;p=56636#p56636"><![CDATA[
Even if no existing cartridge had such a configuration, it would still be electronically possible to do, so you shouldn't impose that kind of restriction anyway.<br /><br />The concept of banks and slots is something that makes easier for us programmers to grasp the concept of bankswitching, but down on the hardware level there is no such thing as slots, it's all about using the address supplied by the CPU to select which part of a memory chip (or chips) will be read. So technically you can even do crazy things like even addresses read from one chip while ood ones read from another.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Mon Feb 15, 2010 6:41 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
