Well, there's no technical requirement that the "slots" should be the same size, so your emulator/whatever shouldn't rely on that. In fact MMC5 for example has a mode (mode #2) where one bank is 16K and other two are 8K: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/MMC5#PRG_mode_.28.245100.29">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/MMC5 ... .245100.29</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Mon Feb 15, 2010 6:09 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
